DOC.brief_summary: The aim of this study is to evaluate whether supplementation with resistant starch improves biomarkers associated with antioxidant status and insulin resistance in subjects with overweight and obesity.
DOC.brief_title: Resistant Starch, Antioxidant Status and Insulin Resistance
DOC.criteria: Overweight and obese adults Age: 2050 years weight loss or gain (more than10%) over the past 6 months, or weight loss (more than 5%) over the past 1 month pregnancy, lactation or menopause History of acute disease or clinical evidence of cancer, acute or chronic inflammatory diseases, cardiovascular disease, renal disease, liver disease, thyroid or endocrine disease Gastrointestinal disease of which ingredients found in the study products have adverse effects on that Use of antihypertensive, lipid lowering or glucose lowering medications Taking antioxidant, vitamin, and/or mineral supplements smoking
